          <LEXSenses>
            <LEXSense LanguageCode="en" LastEdited="2021-02-05 11:15:33" LastEditedBy="">
              <DefinitionLong/>
              <DefinitionShort>to experience a violent attack</DefinitionShort>
              <Glosses>
                <Gloss>to be attacked with violence</Gloss>
                <Gloss>to suffer violent attacks</Gloss>
              </Glosses>
              <Comments>In many languages it may be difficult, if not impossible, to speak of the kingdom of heaven ‘suffering violent attacks,’ but generally some active form may be employed, for example, ‘and violently attack the kingdom of heaven’ or ‘ … the rule of God.’ See comment at βιάζω[b] {D:20.10}.</Comments>
